.TH "epf_ntb_configure_db" 9 "epf_ntb_configure_db" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
epf_ntb_configure_db \- Configure the Outbound Address Space for one host to ring the doorbell of other host
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" epf_ntb_configure_db
.BI "(struct epf_ntb *ntb "  ","
.BI "enum pci_epc_interface_type type "  ","
.BI "u16 db_count "  ","
.BI "bool msix "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ntb" 12
NTB device that facilitates communication between HOST1 and HOST2
.IP "type" 12
PRIMARY interface or SECONDARY interface
.IP "db_count" 12
Count of the number of doorbells that has to be configured
.IP "msix" 12
Indicates whether MSI-X or MSI should be used
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Invokes \fBepf_ntb_configure_msix\fP or \fBepf_ntb_configure_msi\fP required for
one HOST to ring the doorbell of other HOST.
